What is software testing?
-- identify correctness and quality of the application

How many ways we can actually test?
-- manual
-- automation

When do we go for automation?
-- after manual testing passes
-- when the environment is stable
-- analyze our test suite and choose our automation tools

What other automation tools do we know about?
-- Selenium, Cucumber, TestNG, Katalon Studio, Serenity, UFT/QTP

Levels of testing?
-- Unit testing
-- integration testing
-- system testing
-- acceptance testing

Types of software testing?
-- functional testing
    1. smoke test
    2. regression test
    3. sanity check
-- non functional testing
    1. performance testing
    2. security testing

What is Selenium?
-- Selenium is a set of tools that helps us automate web applications. It is mainly used to perform functional testing

Selenium Components:
-- Selenium IDE = integrated development environment
-- Selenium RC = remote control
-- Selenium Grid
-- Selenium WebDriver*

What is Selenium WebDriver?
-- open source automation tool which allows you to perform actions on a web page
-- WebDriver is an interface

Advantages of Selenium WebDriver:
-- open source
-- OS independent
-- supports multiple languages - Ruby, Java, C#, Python
-- works with multiple browsers

Disadvantages of Selenium WebDriver:
-- cant automate desktop applications
-- no technical support
-- does not have builtin reporting feature
-- cant test CAPTCHA/Barcodes

close() vs quit()
-- close() will close the current tab
-- quit() will close the whole browser

navigate() vs get()
-- get() will wait for the whole page to load where as navigate() will not
-- navigate() will move back, forward, and refresh
-- get() will not keep the history of your browser whereas navigate() will